summary: No overlaps or contradictions were found between the provided documents. The primary document is a cost-benefit analysis explaining the rationale for the EBA Guidelines on accounting for expected credit losses. The related documents either refer to and incorporate these guidelines, address different regulatory subjects such as the prudential definition of default, loan origination, or disclosure requirements, or consist of non-operative text like feedback summaries. No instances of divergent or conflicting rules governing the same regulatory subject were identified.
